  "doc_id": "28456",
  "text": "Animal models of neurotrophic and antidepressant function have yielded varied results. A number of lines of BDNF heterozygous (ϩ/Ϫ) knockouts display a reduction in BDNF, but without any accompanying changes in baseline behavior or reactivity to stress. [CITATION_1] Other lines of ϩ/Ϫ BDNF mice display altered synaptic responses but no specific phenotype has been identified. [CITATION_2] These animal lines reveal that a partial loss of BDNF is not enough to affect baseline behavior, but this interpretation is compromised by the fact that these transgenic animals had a loss of BNDF from birth and may have evolved compensatory responses as adults.",
